    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen the terminal is closed which neovim is in, neovim will not close instantly, but linger for around 1-2 seconds and then close.\n\nTested it on Hyprland with terminals: kitty, xterm, alacritty\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n`nvim --clean`\nClose the terminal window (or `:lua vim.uv.kill(vim.api.nvim_get_proc(vim.uv.os_getppid()).ppid,1)`)\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nNeovim closing as soon as the terminal window closes.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.12.0-dev-f89e1eb\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nn/a\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nLinux 6.16.6-arch1-1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.42.2\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo",
